# Exact Version Pinning for Dependencies

All dependencies in this monorepo MUST be added with exact versions. Version ranges (e.g. `^`, `~`, `>=`, `>`, `<`, `<=`, `*`, `x`) are not permitted in `dependencies` or `devDependencies`.

## When adding a new package

- Use `--save-exact` (or `-E`) with pnpm:
  ```
  pnpm add -E <package>
  pnpm add -DE <package>   # for devDependencies
  ```
- If editing `package.json` manually, specify the bare version number only (e.g. `"4.18.4"`, not `"^4.18.4"`).

## Exceptions

- `pnpm.overrides` in the root `package.json` may use ranges when the override is intended to enforce a minimum patched version across transitive dependencies (e.g. security fixes).

## Why

Exact pinning ensures reproducible installs and supports the project's supply chain audit, which rejects any non-exact version in `dependencies` or `devDependencies`.
